eNCA’s Zimbabwe correspondent Pindai Dube has the details. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 HARARE - Zimbabwe’s government say it won’t stop the arrests of human rights and opposition activists, describing them as perennial lawbreakers. Over the past few weeks, Zimbabwe has witnessed several arrests of activists, opposition MDC Alliance members and journalists on different charges. Zimbabwe’s Justice Minister says activists should learn to live with other citizens in peace. eNCA correspondent Pindai Dube has more details in the video above.